com.cloudera.oryx.app.als

Class SolverCache

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.cloudera.oryx.app.als.SolverCache

  • public final class SolverCache
extends Object
    A cache around a Solver that manages computing it when necessary from FeatureVectors, tracking when it must be recomputed, and doing so correctly in the presence of multiple threads.

    • Method Detail

      • setDirty

        public void setDirty()
        Indicates that the underlying FeatureVectors have changed and so the resulting Solver should be recomputed.

      • compute

        public void compute()
        Proactively try to compute the solver asynchronously, if not already computed. Does not block.

      • get

        public Solver get(boolean blocking)
        Parameters:
        blocking - whether to block waiting for a first model
        Returns:
        a recent Solver, optionally blocking if necessary to wait for an initial one to be computed. It does not block otherwise and returns the most recently computed one. Note that this method may return null even when blocking , for instance, if no solver is computable because there is no data.
